I was all packed up and ready to leave yesterday morning and I thought that the clouds where looking really nice. To be honest I just wanted to grab a quick timelapse on my iPhone for my instagram story  but I thought it was worth taking my Nikon out of the bag for a couple of quick shots. I'm glad that I did as there was still a bit of colour left in the sky. It always pays to stick around to see what happens after the sun has come up.

I spent the weekend at St Kilda Beach and it is such a nice place to stay for a few days. I wasn't there to shoot and I didn't get much of a chance to either but I did get this awesome sunset shot when I arrived on the Thursday. St Kilda has a real nice vibe to the place and I loved shooting across the timber promenade. Not to mention the awesome crazy colour in the sky. The layering of texture is what I really love about this shot. Its one of my favourites that I have taken for quite some time.
